Whether you're trying to project future NBA win totals, or simply trying to assemble the best fantasy roster in your office, one of the maddening parts of the process is simply figuring out who is going to play. Luckily, if you are looking for players who could see a lot more of the court this season than last, there are some indicators to point the way. The first step is simply to scan the offseason transaction wire. Which key rotation slots have been vacated? Is there a young player waiting in the wings for that spot? Then you move on to the rosters: Does a team have a cluster of health and/or age risks in a positional group? Is there a glaring skill deficit among the team's top projected six or seven players that can be filled by someone not readily apparent as a rotation option? With those points in mind, let's look at a list of players who might be in line for more minutes this season. Whether it's determined by art or science, there are compelling reasons these 16 players could get sudden surges in their court time: